    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-10-23T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-10-23T18:00:00-05:00" n="705"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d705">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/10–2150: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Korea</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-10-23T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 23, 1950—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>234. Difficult reconcile statements Rhee made to Emb as reported <gloss
                        target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 278, Oct 20 and 284, Oct 21, with his
                    purported interview with <hi rend="italic">US News and World Report</hi>
                    summarized immediate preceding tel.<note n="1" xml:id="d705fn1">Reference is to
                        telegram 232 to Seoul, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> Needless to say,
                    publication interview will again exacerbate relations between UN and Govt <gloss
                        target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> and cannot but operate disadvantage Govt of
                        <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Suggest you strongly urge to Rhee desirability immediately making carefully
                    studied public statement containing points 1, 2, 4, 5, and 6, mentioned <gloss
                        target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 284.</p>
                <p>Point 6 shld be expressed in terms difficulty GOK intelligently cooperating with
                    Interim Comite decisions unless consulted with regard thereto.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d705fn2">
                        <p>The following message was sent to Seoul in telegram 239, October 24, 7 p.
                            m.:</p>
                        <p>“With further ref Deptel 234 Oct 23 any such statement by Rhee shld under
                            point 6 take into account (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) provisional
                            character of Korean <gloss target="#t_IC2">IC</gloss> Oct 12 res,
                            pending <gloss target="#t_UNCURK1">UNCURK</gloss> consideration and (<hi
                                rend="italic">b</hi>) fact it was addressed to Unified Command
                            rather than to <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss>. These circumstances
                            lead us to conclude <gloss target="#t_IC2">IC</gloss> consultation with
                                <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> prior to its adoption was not
                            indispensable.</p>
                        <p>Shld likewise be borne in mind Limb was heard by <gloss target="#t_IC2"
                                >IC</gloss> on Oct 17.” (357.AD/10–2450)</p>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
